  "The energy level and average distance from the nucleus": "",
  "The number of protons": "",
  "The spin of the electron": "",
  "The shape of the orbital": "",
  "The principal quantum number n = 1, 2, 3… indicates the energy level. Higher n means the electron is farther from the nucleus and has greater energy.": "",
  "At which energy level do p orbitals first appear?": "",
  "n = 1": "",
  "n = 2": "",
  "n = 3": "",
  "n = 4": "",
  "The first energy level (n = 1) only has an s orbital. P orbitals begin at n = 2, d orbitals at n = 3, and f orbitals at n = 4.": "",
  "How many orbitals are in a d sublevel?": "",
  "A d sublevel has 5 orbitals, each holding 2 electrons, for a total capacity of 10 electrons. D orbitals start at n = 3.": "",
