  "Orbitals that cannot hold electrons": "",
  "Orbitals that are unstable": "",
  "Orbitals in the nucleus": "",
  "Orbitals that have the same energy level within a sublevel": "",
  "Degenerate orbitals have equal energy. For example, the three 2p orbitals (px, py, pz) are degenerate — electrons fill them singly before pairing (Hund's rule).": "",
