  "A scientist wants to find the exact location of an electron in a hydrogen atom. Why is this impossible according to quantum mechanics?": "",
  "Instruments are not accurate enough yet": "",
  "The Heisenberg Uncertainty Principle prevents knowing exact position and momentum simultaneously": "",
  "Electrons are too large to measure": "",
  "Hydrogen does not have electrons": "",
  "This is a fundamental limit of nature, not a technological one. Measuring position precisely disturbs momentum, making simultaneous exact knowledge of both impossible.": "",
